        "timestamp": "2017-05-15 20:49:59.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nSorry, I'm no maven expert. \nJust seems to me that the sdnc/core/pom.xml is referring to the parent rootpom using a relative path anyways \n(pom.xml line \n    <relativePath>rootpom/pom.xml</relativePath>\n)\n\nwhereas building the \"rootpom\" as a module will make a copy of the \"rootpom\" into the .m2/repository/... directory so it can be accessed by other modules (e.g., dblib - which is where it's failing now without this change).",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "42faff1ad8c4573d22afff2944999e62313b0c5a",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 957,
          "name": "Michael Hansen",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "michael.hansen@amdocs.com",
          "username": "michahan"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-05-16 13:53:23.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIt would seem that the rootpom should be moved up 1 level, to be at the top of the sdnc project? Then the child projects, core, plugins etc. would fall underneath.\nThis would make more logical sense then having the root inside of the dependent child project.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "736dcbd09730d40a784641e68a18c6a36503cc8e",
        "author": {
